    <fr:title text="configuring Safari for viewing a local forest">configuring Safari for viewing a local <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/forester/tfmt-000R.xml" title="forests and trees of evergreen notes" addr="forest://forester/tfmt-000R" type="local">forest</fr:link></fr:title>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter>
    <html:p>To configure Safari for viewing your local <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/forester/tfmt-000R.xml" title="forests and trees of evergreen notes" addr="forest://forester/tfmt-000R" type="local">forest</fr:link>, you must activate the <html:em>Develop</html:em> menu and then toggle one setting.</html:p>
    <html:ol><html:li>Open Safari's settings window.</html:li>
  <html:li>In the <html:em>Advanced</html:em> tab, check the <html:em>“Show Develop menu in menu bar”</html:em> checkbox at the bottom.</html:li>
  <html:li>Open the <html:em>Develop</html:em> menu in the menubar, and select <html:em>“Disable Local File Restrictions”</html:em>.</html:li></html:ol>
  </fr:mainmatter>
