            <fr:title text="viewing your forest locally without a local web server">viewing your <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/forester/tfmt-000R.xml" title="forests and trees of evergreen notes" addr="forest://forester/tfmt-000R" type="local">forest</fr:link> locally without a local web server</fr:title>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>It is also possible to open the generated file <html:code>output/index.xml</html:code> <html:em>directly</html:em> in your web browser. Unfortunately, modern web browsers by default prevent the use of XSLT stylesheets on the local file system for security reasons. Because <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/forester/jms-007G.xml" title="Forester renders each tree to an XML document" addr="forest://forester/jms-007G" type="local"><fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/forester/index.xml" title="Forester" addr="forest://forester/index" type="local">Forester</fr:link>'s output format is XML</fr:link>, the output cannot be viewed directly in your web browser without disabling this security feature (at your own risk). Users who do not understand the risks involved should <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/forester/jms-007I.xml" title="serving and viewing your forest from a local web server" addr="forest://forester/jms-007I" type="local">turn back and use a local web server instead</fr:link>, which is more secure; if you understand and are willing to accept the risks, you may proceed as follows depending on your browser.</html:p>
